<p>What is the length of the unmeasured side of the triangle? <fillin characters="20" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>7.91</li></ul></p><p>Because it does not matter which leg is a and which is b we call the missing leg x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{5.22}^{{2}}={9.48}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{27.2484}={89.8704}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={89.8704}-{27.2484}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={62.622}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{x}^{{2}}}}=\sqrt{{{62.622}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{7.91}</m>.</p>
</solution>
